          %h2 What's included?
          %ul
            %li
              %b Dedicated Service Engineer:
              If anything goes wrong, you’ll know exactly who to reach out to. Your dedicated service engineer
              is your team’s single point of contact for all of their support needs.
            %li
              %b Training:
              Learning a new tool can be challenging, especially if members of your team are also new to Git.
              To ease your team’s transition, you can choose two of the four
              %a{href: "https://about.gitlab.com/training/"}training workshops
              GitLab offers.
            %li
              %b Support for High Availability (HA):
              Your Service Engineer will help you identify your specific HA needs and map out an architecture.
            %li
              %b 24x7 emergency support:
              GitLab responds within 30 minutes to any emergency.
            %li
              %b Live upgrade assistance:
              Schedule an upgrade time with GitLab. We’ll join a live screen share to help you through the process
              and ensure there aren't any surprises.
            %li
              %b Direct access to GitLab's internal chat channel for support:
              Don’t worry about filing a ticket or waiting the standard SLA, simply ask a short or quick questions in
              the channel and receive an almost immediate response.
